"Message from Student Accounts about Refunds MESSAGE FROM STUDENT ACCOUNTS ABOUT REFUNDS

The Office of Student Accounts has begun the refund process. Due to federal regulation, if you have Title IV Federal Funds that creates a credit on your student account, that refund is required to be refunded for the term in which it was paid. If you have a prior balance, this may cause a hold on your account.

If you would like to use your refund to pay a past due balance, payment can be made through your Banner Self-Service portal at my.desu.edu<https://my.desu.edu/>.

If you have any questions, please contact the Office of Student Accounts at [PHONE] or [EMAIL]",0
"Student Account Change February 5, 2026
Denita Jefferson (D10703461)

Dear Denita Jefferson, 

There has been a change to your student account. Changes that affect your student account include (but are not limited to):

     *  Payments/Credits applied to the account
     *  Registering for or dropping a course
     *  Scholarships and Financial aid awarding/disbursement
     *  Student Housing Charges and Housing-related fines
     *  Receiving vouchers for bookstore, laundry, or print
     *  Changes to meal plans/flex dollars
     *  Parking fines, library fines, judicial fines, fire fines, or other penalties assessed

Please log into Banner Self-Service on MyDESU to review your account.

For information about fines assessed to your account, please contact the issuing office (i.e. Residence Life, Public Safety, Library, Policy and Compliance, Judicial Affairs). The contact information for the various areas can be found on the desu.edu website.     For other questions or concerns regarding your account, please contact Student Accounts at (302) 857-6240 and speak to a representative or respond via email to [EMAIL]

Sincerely,

Office of Student Accounts",0
