"Office of Student Accounts Spring 2026 refund process begins OFFICE OF STUDENT ACCOUNTS SPRING 2026 REFUND PROCESS BEGINS

The Office of Student Accounts has begun the Spring 2026 refund process.

Due to federal regulations, if you have Title IV Federal Funds (including Direct Parent Plus Loans, Subsidized and Unsubsidized loans) that creates a credit on your student account, that refund is required to be refunded for the term in which it was paid.

If you have a prior balance, this may cause a hold on your account. Please review your account and make payment for any past due balances.

If you would like to use your refund to pay a past due balance, payment can be made through your Banner Self-Service portal at my.desu.edu<https://my.desu.edu> > Student Services > Hornets Payment Portal.

Important Note: DSU and/or Bank Mobile will never send an email requesting students to verify account information electronically. If you receive such an email, do not click on any links within the message and report the email as Phishing. Should you accidentally click on the links within the message, contact IT at your earliest opportunity and ask that your password be reset.

If you have any questions, please contact the Office of Student Accounts at [PHONE] or [EMAIL]",0
